      <p>
        <s>The given scene from the beginning of the movie <ref target="b10gk1_1" type="title">The Hate U Give</ref> originally written by <name type="person"><choice><orig>angie thomas</orig><reg>Angie Thomas</reg></choice></name> and published in <date>2015</date>, is about the reunion of <ref target="b10gk1_1" type="character">Starr</ref> and <ref target="b10gk1_1" type="character">Chris</ref> as she forgives him.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>The scene starts <choice><orig>of</orig><reg>off</reg></choice> with <ref target="b10gk1_1" type="character">Starr</ref> starring at <ref target="b10gk1_1" type="character">Chris</ref> as he walks down the hallway of their school.</s>
        <s>He <choice><orig>agnowleges</orig><reg>acknowledges</reg></choice> and approaches her.</s>
        <s>They get into an argument about a problem they had in the past but <ref target="b10gk1_1" type="character">Chris</ref> explains his point of view to <ref target="b10gk1_1" type="character">Starr</ref> and she opens up a bit.</s>
        <s>As <ref target="b10gk1_1" type="character">Chris</ref> starts dancing to a beat he made, he feases <ref target="b10gk1_1" type="character">Starr</ref> by dancing to it openly in the hallway and she pulls him to the sides as both of them start laughing.</s>
      </p>
